<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-05-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-05-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="289" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d289">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Chargé <persName type="to">Bailey</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-05-10"><hi rend="italic">May 10,
                                1906</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Root directs Mr. Bailey to express to the Nicaraguan Government, by
                            telegraph, this Government’s sympathy in the loss Nicaragua has
                            sustained in the assassination of its minister of foreign affairs, and
                            its abhorrence of the atrocious deed.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>